SELECT `sys_permissions`.*, `sys_permissions_models`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `sys_permissions_models`.`permission_id` as `pivot_permission_id`, `sys_permissions_models`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` FROM `sys_permissions` inner join `sys_permissions_models` on `sys_permissions`.`id` = `sys_permissions_models`.`permission_id` WHERE `sys_permissions_models`.`model_id` = 1 and `sys_permissions_models`.`model_type` = 'App\\Models\\Auth\\User'

SELECT `sys_roles`.*, `sys_roles_models`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `sys_roles_models`.`role_id` as `pivot_role_id`, `sys_roles_models`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` FROM `sys_roles` inner join `sys_roles_models` on `sys_roles`.`id` = `sys_roles_models`.`role_id` WHERE `sys_roles_models`.`model_id` in (1) and `sys_roles_models`.`model_type` = 'App\\Models\\Auth\\User'
